values: God save Jack Kerouac. God save spontaneous prose. All red hair and red lips, the goddess in the closet pronounces sweet freedom -- concern etched on her face by an unseen sketcher -- am I going crazy or is this some kind of practical joke? Thin lips stretch the syllables -- she's manic, I'm manic, everyone's manic but the cat in the tree -- there's always a fucking cat up the fucking tree, chasing whatever they bought at the butcher shop today. In her little cubby hole, I was spontaneously struck by the sensation of strangulation -- thick air, humid like a summer in New York -- going two-hundred miles per hour in the wrong direction -- on a one-way street -- and someone just smashed a raw egg over my head. He's a fucking sponge, I swear to god. And there are pixies everywhere. Only one has an altar though -- I think I need to do this more often -- Alexander Pope has lodged himself in my ear canal with a miniature mock-up of her -- blue eyes turn green and the last Sacagawea's spent up. I am spent up. This too shall become habitual.

Behold as Leslie makes things up off the top of our collective head! (!) What did he/she have for breakfast today? Coffee. He's currently protesting the notion that only feminists and Gandhi can go without food. He's been doing this since approximately 3 AM. Yesterday, he had coffee and a vegan brownie for breakfast. Mikey told him to eat real food; he made a lame joke about oral sex in return. Either way, he always gets breakfast at the coffee house (sometimes Coney Island). What's in his pockets? His wallet, which is, in turn, stuffed with: a driver's license he doesn't need, a Metrocard from his one trip to New York, a well-past expired Wayne State student ID that still works, more library cards than anyone could ever need, a few Sacagawea dollars, a few crumpled singles, and a crisp fifty from his mom (who still hasn't gotten over how her baby boy is completely off his nut and blames her). Also in his pockets are: pens, spare change, vegan chapstick, a coupon for fast food that he took because he felt sorry for the dumbass in the taco suit, a Cheez-It, a shoelace, and a coupon for free Ben & Jerry's that he never redeemed. What is his/her most treasured item? His flamboyant, brightly-colored scarf (his grandma made it for him just before she died), his black beret (his older sister bought it for him in France, back when she didn't get exasperated and tell their parents that he was on drugs), and his microwave (first thing he bought with his own money... also, it melts cheese).

And an unofficial one for my own use (specifically: Troy, Vince & Hale, Are We Having Fun Yet?-verse, and prosetry). I'm putting it here anyway because it's an exercise in minimalism, ergo valid. (; Snape/Crouch Jr.)
